The paper deals with codes for storage systems, which are typically studied in the information theory (cs.IT) and distributed systems (cs.DS) communities. The focus on optimal bandwidth and access suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the data compression (cs.DC) and signal processing (cs.SI) communities. Finally, the use of nodes and capacity suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the networking and internet architecture (cs.NI) community.
